1
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:34,600
Why hasn't the food I ordered arrived yet?

2
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:39,259
Why is everyone looking down at this?

3
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:41,800
Nowadays, all information,

4
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:44,930
including the most important data, is stored in phones.

5
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:47,280
It's a tool modern people can't live without.

6
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:48,240
Exactly.

7
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:50,240
It's a lifesaver for modern people.

8
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:52,440
Without it, it's like losing your soul.

9
00:01:53,479 --> 00:01:54,720
All information,

10
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,200
everything in the world,

11
00:01:58,039 --> 00:02:00,360
can be received immediately through this.

12
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:01,280
Immediately?

13
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:04,840
Oh.

14
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:05,760
Come here.

15
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:07,400
I'll teach you directly.

16
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:11,760
The hard work of today's young people is meaningless.

17
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:13,520
Rat race is just self-torture.

18
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:15,480
Lying flat is the true meaning of life.

19
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:16,680
With a salary of 3,000 yuan,

20
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:17,320
what are you worrying about?

21
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,960
This is not very appropriate.

22
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:19,480
Wait.

23
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:21,840
What did this person say?

24
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,800
What's wrong?

25
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:28,160
Why did he say the hard work of young people is meaningless?

26
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:30,560
It's his personal opinion.

27
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:32,420
And what he said makes some sense.

28
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:35,500
You actually think what he said makes sense?

29
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,000
Oh.

30
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,840
There is freedom of speech now.

31
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:38,520
What?

32
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:40,050
Do you want to convince him?

33
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,040
Convince him?

34
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:43,480
I really want to have a conversation with him.

35
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:44,400
I want to ask him

36
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,130
how he came to this conclusion.

37
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:49,720
Can't you see it immediately with this?

38
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:52,440
What?

39
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:54,170
Do you want to connect with him?

40
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,970
I want to talk to him.

41
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:57,000
Use this.

42
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:59,079
Yaoyao.

43
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:01,170
We can connect and livestream now.

44
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:05,040
Are you sure?

45
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:08,040
If I press this, you can talk to him.

46
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:09,440
Should I be afraid of him?

47
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:11,320
That's what I've been waiting for.

48
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,040
Wait a moment.

49
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:13,120
Just face this

50
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,880
and say whatever you want.

51
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:16,160
But one thing,

52
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:18,360
you can't get angry and smash the phone.

53
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:26,220
My dear followers,

54
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:29,280
I'll connect with my bro 'Yijiu Taoxin'.

55
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,040
Okay?

56
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:31,520
Let's connect.

57
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,600
This is a username.

58
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,160
Hello.

59
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:35,960
Yijiu Taoxin.

60
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,440
Was it you who just made those remarks

61
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,370
teaching young people to lie flat?

62
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:40,920
Then let me ask you,

63
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:42,380
what does lying flat mean?

64
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:43,040
What?

65
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:46,280
This word is not unfamiliar, right?

66
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,640
Do I need to explain more?

67
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:50,280
I only know that I'd rather die of exhaustion standing up,

68
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:51,610
than choose to lie flat.

69
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,960
Here comes a contrarian.

70
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:56,720
You are talking about a beast of burden, right?

71
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,680
Then let me ask you again,

72
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:01,210
does being blown to death count as lying flat?

73
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:02,680
Bro,

74
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,360
what you said is too serious.

75
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,800
Lying flat comfortably is so nice.

76
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,530
Why choose to be blown to death?

77
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,800
Then tell me,

78
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,600
what is comfortably lying flat?

79
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:14,800
Man,

80
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,360
are you a repeater?

81
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:17,880
Do you have to make me say it?

82
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:21,399
Enjoying AC, watching TV, scrolling the phone, eating fruit,

83
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:23,930
that's what you call comfortable lying flat?

84
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:27,720
Your words are simply abhorrent.

85
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:30,080
Back then, we risked our lives to transport supplies,

86
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:32,240
some even died on the way.

87
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:33,040
For what?

88
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:35,080
To drive the invaders out

89
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:36,810
so we wouldn't suffer anymore.

90
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,000
Tell me,

91
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,440
is that lying flat?

92
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:40,560
Now,

93
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:41,720
you tell young people

94
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,120
that hard work is meaningless

95
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,580
and teach them to lie flat.

96
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:46,480
Have you ever thought

97
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:48,080
if our generation lay flat,

98
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:50,400
would you be here to say this today?

99
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,100
Transporting supplies back then...

100
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,000
What era is this?

101
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,159
Still talking about the past?

102
00:04:56,159 --> 00:04:57,890
I'm afraid you live in the past.

103
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,480
Man,

104
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:01,480
what right do you have to lecture me?

105
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,800
Right?

106
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:06,720
Look.

107
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,050
Do you know what this is?

108
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,160
You don't.

109
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:11,840
This is a scar from dodging Japanese bombs.

110
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,360
I risked my life.

111
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:15,890
Does that give me the right?

112
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:18,080
If we had chosen to lie flat,

113
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:20,320
why would I bother returning to my country?

114
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,640
How many compatriots died under Japanese swords?

115
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:23,480
Do you know?

116
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:25,840
If our people had chosen to lie flat,

117
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,700
would there be today's New China?

118
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,480
The 'lying flat' you talk about now,

119
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,480
do you know

120
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:32,159
we paid for it with our lives?

121
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:36,320
Also,

122
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:37,880
I want to ask you,

123
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,010
is your job to teach people to lie flat?

124
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:42,140
I didn't teach anyone to lie flat.

125
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:44,159
Many people work 996 now,

126
00:05:44,159 --> 00:05:45,400
with high pressure.

127
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:46,880
I was just joking.

128
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:47,940
Is it that serious?

129
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,640
I think you are sick.

130
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:54,560
Well,

131
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:56,960
I am still your honest friend.

132
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:58,560
This is my friend.

133
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:00,680
You might not believe it,

134
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:03,760
but I swear on Zhang Yiyi's dignity,

135
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:07,600
he time-traveled from 1941.

136
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,160
It's absolutely true.

137
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,200
I've tested him.

138
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,530
If you don't believe it,

139
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:12,880
you can test him.

140
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,440
The number of viewers is going up.

141
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:19,040
Hurry.

142
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,970
I am Lin Yaozu, a mechanic returned from Nanyang.

143
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:26,970
The 'joke' that young man just mentioned,

144
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:29,480
what a joke!

145
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,760
The life we have now

146
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:34,220
is something we didn't even dare to dream of.

147
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:36,240
If millions of Chinese sons and daughters back then

148
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,680
only thought of surviving ignobly,

149
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:40,120
begging like traitors,

150
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:42,920
would we have today's prosperity?

151
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:46,640
Can this phone capture the resolve to die for our country?

152
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:49,480
Can it capture the passion of building roads with our flesh and blood?

153
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:52,520
Can it capture that perilous transport route?

154
00:06:53,159 --> 00:06:53,960
A joke?

155
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,340
What right do you have to joke?

156
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,120
Of course.

157
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:03,480
I know everyone has their own viewpoint.

158
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:04,960
Every era

159
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,400
has its own right values.

160
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,280
Your era

161
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:13,480
has the peace that we couldn't have in ours,

162
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:15,320
knowledge, and wealth.

163
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:19,560
You have the life we once dreamed of.

164
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,920
You are fortunate to be born in such an era.

165
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:27,360
The energy within you is unimaginable.

166
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:31,520
Only those with a weak heart will choose to lie flat.

167
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:34,680
Those with a strong heart will not surrender to fate.

168
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:38,400
Because the hope of this country lies in the youth.

169
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,120
You said it very well.

170
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:44,240
Our era should have correct viewpoints.

171
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,560
When we are bullied,

172
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,440
the blood in our bones will awaken.

173
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:50,840
Because we are awakened youth.

174
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,520
100,000 followers.

175
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:01,800
Look how excited you are.

176
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:06,600
This traffic is enough for him to sleep on the sofa for a few days, right?

177
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,200
Look at what you're saying.

178
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:10,400
How about I give up the bed for him to sleep in,

179
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:11,660
and I sleep on the sofa?

180
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:16,080
Is this thing of yours really that important?

181
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,000
Of course.

182
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,720
This shows that many people see you.

183
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:21,440
And the final voices of support are one-sided,

184
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:24,280
which shows that many people support your viewpoint.

185
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:25,540
Support my viewpoint?

186
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:28,280
Everyone has their own viewpoint,

187
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:30,880
but at least it should be correct and positive.

188
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:33,600
Awakened youth.
